  "texts": [
    "It is worthy of note that since contemporary novels and government documents are typically very long texts consisting of relatively independent chapters or sections of a certain length, we took relatively shorter samples from the long texts without compromising the integrity and homogeneity of the contents.",
    "Indicators for simplification.",
    "Since the goal of this study is to test whether simplification found in human translations also exists in machine translations, type-token ratio (TTR), an indicator commonly examined in corpus-based studies of human translations, is chosen to achieve the research goal.",
    "TTR is the ratio of unique words (types) that occur in a text to the total number of words (tokens) (McEnery and Hardie, 2011; McNamara et al., 2014).",
    "A higher TTR indicates that most words in a text are different, i.e., more new words are used."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "TTR is the ratio of unique words (types) that occur in a text to the total number of words (tokens) (McEnery and Hardie, 2011; McNamara et al., 2014)."
  ]
